  "text": "The Prometheus TSDB write-ahead log (WAL) implementation spans multiple Go source files in the prometheus/prometheus repository, organized around segment management, record encoding/decoding, and WAL replay. **Core WAL Implementation (tsdb/wlog/):** The `wlog.go` file contains the main WL (Write Log) type that manages WAL segment creation and rotation. Key functions include `CreateSegment()` and `OpenWriteSegment()` for segment creation, `NextSegment()` and `NextSegmentSync()` for segment rotation, and the `Repair()` method for handling corrupted segments. The WL type uses a page-based buffering system (32KB pages) with automatic segment rotation when records would exceed segment boundaries, ensuring no records cross segment boundaries. Segments are stored as numbered files (00000000, 00000001, etc.) and can be efficiently truncated via the `Truncate()` method. **Record Encoding (tsdb/record/record.go):** The record package defines the WAL record format with separate types for different data: RefSeries (series definitions), RefSample (float samples), RefMetadata (metric metadata), RefExemplar (exemplars), RefHistogramSample (histogram samples), and RefFloatHistogramSample (float histogram samples). The Encoder type provides methods for encoding each record type (`Series()`, `Samples()`, `Metadata()`, `Tombstones()`, `HistogramSamples()`, etc.) using a binary format with delta encoding for timestamps and reference numbers. The Decoder type provides corresponding decoding methods and can identify record types. **Checkpoint Creation (tsdb/wlog/checkpoint.go):** The `Checkpoint()` function creates compacted checkpoints of WAL segments to truncate old WAL data. It reads from a specified range of segments, filters out old data (based on timestamp and series filters), and writes a new checkpoint directory containing the relevant records in the same WAL format. The `LastCheckpoint()` function retrieves the most recent checkpoint, and `DeleteCheckpoints()` removes